8.3. Definition of an Adverse Event:
An AEis any untoward medical occurrence in a clinical investigation patient administered a
product or medical device; the event need not necessarily have a causal relationship with the
treatment or usage. Examples of AEs include but are not limited to:
• Abnormal test findings;
• Clinicallysignificant symptoms and signs;
• Changes in physical examination findings;
• Hypersensitivity;
• Drug abuse;
• Drug dependency.
